cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.GR, cs.LG

This paper discusses an algorithm for accelerating the implementation of bilateral filtering and non-local means, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves signal processing and optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the use of trigonometric functions and their shiftability property could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the proposed modifications for accelerating the implementation could be considered as a form of machine learning, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
